license: CC-BY-4.0
abstract: >
  Top-K sparse attention is widely deployed on the implicit premise that there is a
  key budget below which long-context ability collapses. Using a training-free,
  exact-ranking query-axis selector on Llama-3.2-1B, Qwen2.5-3B and Llama-3.2-3B, we
  decouple the absolute key budget from context length and show the budget is inert
  (a 4x swing moves accuracy by <=0.03 at any length), refuting an absolute critical
  capacity. The long-context limit is the base model's own disambiguation; capacity
  raises that ceiling without creating a budget threshold. A matched-control causal
  probe shows attention here is transport, not computation. There is no efficiency
  cliff in the compressor within the practical operating regime.
